quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  37,1,"By those aligned, lined up in ranks."
  37,2,"Then by the propellers propelling firmly."
  37,3,"Then by the readers of a Reminder—"
  37,4,"indeed, your<sup>pl </sup>God is surely One,"
  37,5,"Lord of the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them, and Lord of the Easts."
  37,6,"Indeed, We have adorned the lowest{1}heaven withan adornment, the planets{2},",footnotes:1:[The Arabic word <i>dunya</i> translated here as “lowest” is the same word used to describe the life of this world as the “Earlier” Life, as it carries both meanings: lowest and earlier.],footnotes:2:[Qira’at: Shu’ba read it as: “We have adorned the lower heaven by adorning the planets,” All except for Shu’ba, Hafs and Hamza read it as: “We have adorned the lower heaven with the adornment of planets,”]
  37,7,"and as a protection against every defiant devil."
  37,8,"They cannot eavesdrop{1}onthe Higher Assembly, for they get bombarded from every side—",footnotes:1:Qira’at: All except for Hafs, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “They cannot hear the Higher…”
  37,9,"repelled, and they will have an unremitting punishment,"
  37,10,"except for one who snatched a fragment and was then pursued by a piercing meteor."
